---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Tenders"
  description="Give your tender documents the best chance of success. Lynden Howells reviews tenders for omissions, contradictions, layout issues, and errors that can result in rejection."
>
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Tender Documents</h1>
      <p class="page-header__sub">Give your tenders the best possible chance of success</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>Why tenders fail</h2>
      <hr class="gold-rule" />
      <p>
        Quotes and tenders are rejected on technicalities every day. A confusing layout,
        a contradictory clause, a missed requirement, a grammatical error — any of these
        can undermine a submission that is otherwise technically strong.
      </p>
      <p>
        The people evaluating your tender are looking for reasons to narrow the field.
        Don't hand them one.
      </p>

      <h2>What I look for</h2>
      <hr class="gold-rule" />
      <p>
        I have been thoroughly trained in spotting the kinds of errors, omissions, and
        anomalies that evaluators notice — and I don't need to be a subject matter expert
        in your field to do this effectively. In fact, fresh eyes often see what familiarity
        blinds you to.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Confusing or inconsistent layout and structure</li>
        <li>Contradictions between sections</li>
        <li>Omissions — requirements from the brief that haven't been addressed</li>
        <li>Lack of thoroughness in responding to specific evaluation criteria</li>
        <li>Grammatical errors and spelling mistakes</li>
        <li>Ambiguous phrasing that could be read against you</li>
        <li>Formatting and numbering inconsistencies</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="highlight-box">
        <p style="font-size:1.05rem;font-style:italic;margin:0;">
          "Send it to me first and your chances of success will increase. Dramatically."
        </p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-weight:700;font-size:0.9rem;">— Lynden Howells</p>
      </div>

      <h2>That's my job. That's my passion.</h2>
      <hr class="gold-rule" />
      <p>
        Tender documents are high-stakes. The time invested in having them reviewed
        by a professional is small compared to the value of the contract you're pursuing.
      </p>
      <p>
        I work quickly and discreetly. Send me your document and I'll give you an honest
        assessment of what I find — and what it would cost to fix it.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-2"><a href="/contact" class="btn">Discuss Your Tender</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
